It seems like a couple more fight this year would do him well before he fight the top 4-6 fighters in his division. I would like to see his adopt a more natural bob and weave technique and a better counter punching technique along with his flurry of combos. He was able to recognize when he should lay off of Sullivan vs just keeping on swinging from the fences. A lot of little improvements will make a big difference in the long run.
